In addition, the following @command{rpm} options, specific to the @value{PACKAGE_TITLE} package are
available:

@table @command

@item --without SCTP
@opindex SCTP

When disabled, excludes the @command{sctp-@value{VERSION_SCTP}} add-on package from the build.
This function is useful only for disabling build of the @command{sctp} add-on package on a 2.4
series @cite{Linux} kernel.
This option defaults differently depending upon for which kernel the add-on package is being built.
For 2.4 kernels, this option defaults to include the @command{sctp} add-on package; 2.6 kernels,
defaults to exclude the @command{sctp} add-on package.

@item --without IPERF
@opindex IPERF

When disabled, excludes the @command{iperf-@value{VERSION_IPERF}} add-on package from the build.
This function is useful only for disabling build of the @command{sctp} add-on package on a 2.4
series @cite{Linux} kernel.
This option defaults differently depending upon for which kernel the add-on package is being built.
For 2.4 kernels, this option defaults to include the @command{sctp} add-on package; 2.6 kernels,
defaults to exclude the @command{sctp} add-on package.

@item --without STREAMS
@opindex STREAMS

When disabled, excludes the @command{streams-@value{VERSION_STREAMS}} add-on package from the build.
When the @command{streams} add-on package is excluded, none of the packages which depend upon it
can be built unless the @command{streams} package was otherwise installed on the build system.
The default is to include the
@cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} (@command{streams-@value{VERSION_STREAMS}})
add-on package in the build.

